      "term": "acrospire",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C2",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "The first young shoot that grows from the top of a germinating grain seed, especially in barley used for malting.",
          "examples": [
            "The maltster checked the length of the acrospire during germination.",
            "If the acrospire grows too long, the grain may lose too much starch for brewing."
          ],
          "collocations": [
